# Explantion
1. if both the nodes are null return *true*
2. one of the nodes are null return *false*
3. if values of both nodes are not same return *false*
4. call left and right child for both the nodes.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n), where, n is the number of nodes
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
