* Overall the idea is to find **number of connected components**
* If adjacent cell is having 1, consider it as a **connected node** 
* Being at any (i,j) point , apply DFS recursively to all its connected nodes
* You can either take a visited matrix or modify the same matrix making 1 as 0 ( I have modified the same matrix)
* DFS is like, if u burn a points, it will burn all the points connected, u need to count how much time u need to burn such that all points are burnt 
* **TC: (N*M)**  ( Explained more in comment section )
* **SC: (N*M)**

